cs.IR, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.MM, cs.LG 

This paper is about cross-modal retrieval, which involves multiple modalities such as text, image, and audio. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR), Computer Vision (cs.CV), Computational Linguistics (cs.CL), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Among these, cs.IR is the most likely category as the paper focuses on retrieval tasks. cs.CV and cs.CL are also likely categories as the paper deals with image and text modalities. cs.MM is also a possible category as the paper deals with multimedia data. Finally, cs.LG is a possible category as the paper proposes a novel approach for learning representations.
